author: @dont_trip_over_ma_leg_please
text: I love seventeen choreographies but this one I keep coming back to. It is ever so beautiful in the way it some actions or images are intrinsically connected to the lyrics, and the whole emotion conveyed it just spot on. Some of my favourite parts are when a couple members are having a solo or small group moment in the centre and it flows seamlessly from one small group to another, and then comes back to the whole team. I also love the part where it’s a group of them in the middle, and then the rest are in a circle around the outside doing a different choreography, same with the other times they split and different sections all do different moves. I feel a lot of the way they slot together is almost like this ancient puzzle piece type thing where you can shift the pieces around and it still looks just as cool - likely a testament to their skills as dancers, their teamwork and also the meticulousness of the choreographer. A truly stunning piece of art!

author: @ドヨン-z1s
text:
레투럽 내가 좋아하는 권순영 춤추는 부분

0:35 권호시 파트 시작 이미 춤선도 너무 미쳤음
0:45 어깨 탁탁 터는데 강약 조절 미쳤음
0:47 모자 고쳐 쓰고 후렴? 부분 준비 들어가는 부분 너무 멋있음
1:12 여기 내 최애1 부분  뭔가 다리 뻗고 손짓 그리고 뒤 돌면서 가슴 쿵쿵 하는데 ㅈㄹ 멋있음 뭔가 가끔 생각나서 이 파트만 보러 자주 옴
2:08 뒤 돌면서 걸어 나가는 권순영 ㅈㄴ 멋있음 걍 멋짐 
2:21 밍구랑 거의 바깥쪽 끝까지 갔다가 전속력으로 안쪽으로 들어올때 보이는 그 강약조절이 너무 신기함
2:32 자기 파트 할려고 걸어나오는 부분 그냥 압도감 미침
2:36 내 차애 파트,, 이 부분 강약조절은 권순영이 짱인 것 같다,, 진짜 위로 뻗고 밑까지 내려와서 또 빨리 다음 동작하는데 진짜 어떻게 저렇게 빠르게 움직일까,,  뭔가 독기? 라고 해야 되나? 그렇게 다크한 분위기는 아니지만 빡세게 추는게 보여서(항상 빡세게 추는거 알지만) 안무 영상 보는데 뭔가 내가 다 희열을 느낀다,,
2:44 무릎 따악 세우고 고개도 그냥 정면 아니고 살짝 턱 위로 올린 고개라서 그냥 미침,,

그냥 호시 파트 아닌 부분이어도 너무 좋은 부분이 많아서 (제가 보기에) 정리 해서 올림 
호랑해🐹❤

author: @SD-gn7xf
text:
Omg I’ve been trying to zoom out and watch the whole choreo but my eyes just keep going on to Hoshi and mingyu😭 this choreo just suits them so much 🥹 also, I’ve been noticing but it’s just been made more evident ever since I saw the 97 line covering light a flame, that for someone who is so huge and buff, mingyu is SO GOOD at choreos that are suppose to deliver a softer vibe! Like…I would expect someone as big as him to be able to deliver powerpacked choreos and moves but when he performs these dances with a softer vibe, with movements that require grace, he somehow delivers almost effortlessly and he ends up making the choreo seem more…sensual?!? Like idk…I just wanna keep watching him do those kind of movements which require you to bend ur limbs and body line finely and with grace like the hook step (and most of the choreo) of light a flame and ready to love and fall in flower😳😍🤤🤤🤤
EDIT: OMG GUYS at 1:59, the centres, they literally have to lower themselves on ONE LEG🤯 I cannot IMAGINE the leg strength required to execute that and that too so in sync?🤯

EDIT 2: OMG at 2:19 I think, like when the bridge starts and they all fold in behind Seungkwan? ITS SO BEAUTIFUL 😭 the breathlessness of the song is legit delivered through the choreo too!! Bro how are we ever suppose to notice these details in the music show performances?! It’s too much, that’s why SVT dance videos are an absolute MUST! I feel like their dance practices could acc have a fandom of their own lol

author: @applepie980
text:
I've just realized but ready to love has a lot of running (idk what it's called but they look like running to me) choreo. Some members, they change their places a lot of times in the song. 

Another one i realized, is in the part right before dk and seungkwan's high note, the members are lined up and holding onto each other's hands but when dk moves from the back to front the hands let go one by one until the last pair(?) Only has their fingers touch each other and then they also let go. It's kinda interesting bc the eng translation of the lyrics in that part is 'i don't wanna waste anymore' . Maybe the person 'don't wanna waste anymore' bc it'd too late if they waste more time to tell the other person that they're 'ready to love'. 

And before that part, where the lyrics are 'With each passing day, my emotions keep growing' the members are lining up one by one in pairs while doing some gestures like holding their heads or reaching out i think it conveys the feeling of "emotions keep growing" really well.. 

And in the end, after scoups line 'I want to run for you' the instrumental and choreo just pops out with all of the members dancing the same choreo, different in comparison to the first chorus and second chorus just gives me a feeling like it's a burst of emotion at the end..,


Honestly idk what i've just wrote,, but i guess it's some of my thoughts abt the choreo(?)

author: @tellme2584
text:
I'll be honest with u guys. I don't really like this choreography. 
 Its not unique and satisfying, like others choreos they have done before. Ready To Love is a ballad song just like Don't Wanna Cry but you can see the different between these two choreography where DWC looks so catchy, unique, has sign language and we can sense their emotion through any movements in its choreo. But this RTL choreo lacks those things i said. I saw a comment in another video that says Keone madrid made this choreography. That's why i kinda have this "it isn't really Seventeen vibe" feeling. I'm not talking about the members anyway (they're amazing dancers and can pull any type of choreography). It's just the choreo. This choreo is pretty powerful but somehow not catchy at all. It doesn't show off their emotion and uniqueness. 
I want Hoshi & performance team and CYJ to create the choreo instead. I hope Hybe doesn't mess with them
(idk if any of you can feel what i feel toward this choreo)

author: @oktawidanti5867
text:
Analisa Choreo SVT - Ready to Love by Brandon:
1. Berhasil menyamakan feeling gerakan, karena susah nyamain feeling di grup yg byk member
2. Formation super bagus, ngeliat ga bosen
3. Meski member banyak, berani main formasi kecil
4. Komposisi formasi dan tarian ga too much
5. Creative dlm milih gerakan
6. Direction yg beda, dengan gerakan yg sama
7. Bru 50 detik, ga perlu 100% power tapi dominan di texture
8. "mereka kalau nari kayak satu badan banget" 
9. Style lagu apapun bisa nyesuain dancenya
10. Intinya, ancen apik! bagus banget!

author: @spoonsmcgee6365
text:
My fave parts of the choreo:
-The embrace at the start + some of the members running in a circle whilst the rest stand. 
-That canon part at 0:40 I adore canon parts in choreos. 
-The arm bit at “run away” in the chorus. I just love the way that line is sung too ughhh
-That cool ass pulsating move at 1:50 it mimics the beat super well. Like it looks how the beat sounds to me???  
- the split group walk thing at 2:06
-That hella cool mirror image pair canon part at 2:20 FR THAT IS SO GORGEOUS I AM OBSESSED. 
-The last part just because last chorus’ are always full of energy and just so fun to watch!! 

Last but not least my fave part is...
-the entire choreo. Just all of it.

Also love how the members run at the start of the choreo and also at the end, kinda randomly like there’s no true destination. It comes full circle and echoes the “run away” lyric in the song and running from love. Very much love when the choreo relates to some of the lyrics :))

author: @am_rima
text:
You all know what super impressive from SEVENTEEN though, is the fact that this choreography in general has a lot of running, changing formation, and like control movements where they appear all smooth, strong/powerful/ and very detailed, like you can literally see each and every part of their body moving and dancing to the music BUT!! still MANAGE to sing and rap with such stability.... like that's full on professionalism. When their part comes up in like the live performances, they appear like they were not just doing a bunch of running or dancing, it's as if they have been waiting for their part for long that that ONE quick moment of their line is very memorable.

I can easily see and have a good moment for each member's parts on this song and I'm honestly impressed even after what? 7 years since pre-debut era in 2013 hahah 👏🏻💞✨

author: @luvletter93
text: SVT really setting the bar at what 'synchronization' really is. And also being a big group, they ALWAYS make use of that advantage in making their choreos stand out from the rest, like how they're running from their spot to the others while matching the lyrics - just simply genius. 6 years on and I know I shouldn't be surprised by just how good they are at this point but they amaze me every single time. So proud of these boys💙

author: @am_rima
text:
That was....wow😭✨👏🏻 I'm actually like speechless even though I've been a fan since 2013. Their performance and formation are so perfect and smooth that I'm honestly super grateful and happy to be a CARAT. We really got it good guys 😭😭😭 SEVENTEEN is always treating us so good and I'm super happy and really just... ugh. I started crying in the middle of the video.. I didn't want to but I just had this whole flashback of SEVENTEEN since debut to now and I'm just really grateful to be part of SEVENTEEN's life as a carat. 

SEVENTEEN x CARAT let's work hard on this era!
Stay safe and healthy everyone ❤️‍🔥

I just want to say 5 things...

First thing... When it was S-coups line " Cause you are my escape " and the way they pop their shoulders and are in sync is so fascinating

Second thing... Giving the youngest aka Dino his center performance is just so cute.

Third thing... The performance and energy they give are so empowering and powerful. It makes the song have a lot of meaning to it

Fourth thing... The concept and the outfits for this song is just so fitting and I love how true they are when they're performing

The 5th and final thing... They are such perfectionists and they make their dance look so easy but it's not.
